list.name: Ottawa’s Homeless Period
list.description: <p>Chisomo F Nguluwe is a graduate of Algonquin College and the Founder of Ottawa’s Homeless Period which is a community project aimed at making feminine sanitary products accessible to homeless women in Ottawa. She is a staunch advocate for the empowerment of women and she is driven by a deep desire to play her part </p>\n

list.name: NCRCFE Croatoan: 39th Annual Spring Concert
list.description: <p>The National Capital Region Croatian Folklore Ensemble presents their 39th Annual Spring Concert. Doors Open 12:15pm Event Start 12:30pm Tickets $8.50 – General Admission General admission seating. All tickets are final sale. No exchanges or refunds. Children aged 3 and under may attend the event at no cost, (with no ticket), provided they sit on a parent’s lap </p>\n

list.name: Home Free – Don’t It Feel Good
list.description: <p>Join us in the Algonquin Commons Theatre September 19th for an evening of a cappella entertainment! Capital City Chorus, a premiere a cappella mens chorus, will get the night started. Followed by Season 4 Champions of NBC\'s The Sing-Off, Home Free! Show One Lobby Opens 1:30pm | Doors Open 2:00pm | Event Start 2:30pm Show Two Lobby Opens </p>\n
